cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MA, cs.PF

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with wireless cellular networks and handover-based mobility state detection, which falls under the purview of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper uses statistical analysis and derives approximations to the Cramer-Rao lower bound, which is a concept from information theory. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with the problem of detecting the mobility state of a UE, which can be seen as a control problem in a wireless network system. 
4. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The paper models small cells using stochastic geometry, which can be seen as a multiagent system. 
5. cs.PF (Performance) - The paper evaluates the accuracy of the velocity estimator under different scenarios, which can be seen as a performance analysis.
